biomaterial_provider: Leung lab, Hong Kong University of Science and Technology
collection_method: The animal was deeply anesthetized with Avertin (0.03 ml/g); the depth of anesthesia was assessed by the absence of deep tendon reflexes following a strong foot pinch.  Once adequate anesthesia was achieved, the chest cavity was opened. The right atrium was clipped to allow exsanguination and the mouse was perfused through the left ventricle with PBS. Whole brain was obtained and cut into the left and right hemispheres. Each half was then dissected separately by eye. Hindbrain and cerebellum was first separated from the hemispheres, then cerebellum was obtained. The olfactory bulb was removed, along with brain stem regions until hippocampus was clearly visible. Hippocampus was obtained, and the remaining tissue was labelled as cerebral cortex. All collected tissue was snap frozen and stored at -80C until nuclei extraction. For nuclei extraction, frozen tissue was added to 1 mL cold 1X homogenization buffer (320 mM sucrose, 0.1 mM EDTA, 0.1% NP40, 5 mM CaCl2, 3 mM Mg(Ac)2, 10 mM Tris pH 7.8, 16.7 M PMSF, 167 M -mercaptoethanol, 1U/mL RNAse inhibitor in nuclease-free water) (modified from Corces et al., 2017). Tissue was dounced 10 strokes using loose pestle and 5 strokes using tight pestle (WHEATON Dounce Tissue Grinder, 1 mL). Homogenate was filtered through a 40 m cell strainer and spun down at  4C, 1000g for 10 mins. Pellet was resuspended in 3mL of low sucrose buffer (0.32M sucrose, 10mM HEPES pH 8, 5mM CaCl2, 3mM Mg(Ac)2, 0.1mM EDTA, 1mM DTT, 0.2U/L RNAse inhibitor in nuclease-free water) (modified from Matson et al., 2018). 12.5 mL of sucrose density buffer (1M sucrose, 10mM HEPES pH 8, 3mM Mg(Ac)2, 1mM DTT in nuclease-free water) was added slowly underneath the low sucrose buffer homogenate. The sucrose gradient was then centrifuged in a swing-bucket rotor at 4C, 3200g for 20 min. The supernatant was decanted and pelleted purified nuclei was resuspended in buffer for sorting (0.2U/L RNAse inhibitor, 1% BSA in PBS). Nuclei was stained with Hoechst at 2g/uL.
label: NaN
notes_on_tissue: The most inclusive ontology term was used, but not all regions in the ontology are present in the tissue. Under telencephalon (ontology hierarchy), this sample is best represented by cerebral grey matter, cerebral hemisphere and cerebral white matter.
